{"title":"Michelin refresh the all-mountain lineup with DH-inspired Wild AM2 & Force AM2","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/16/michelin-refresh-the-all-mountain-lineup-with-dh-inspired-wild-am2-force-am2/","date":1613469617000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Michelin have announced the long-overdue refresh of two all-mountain tires, releasing the 2021 Force AM2 and Wild AM2 tires with all-new DH-inspired tread patterns. The Michelin Force AM2 and Wild AM2 offer very distinct treads that convey their intention for aggressive trail and all-mountain riding. Both get EWS-proven dual compound GUM-X rubber and 3 x 60 TPI casing with Gravity Shield Technology. Here’s everything you need to know.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bz8fhI_dKoA?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\"></iframe></span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire.jpg\" alt=\"2021 michelin wild am2 all mountain bike tire side profile shoulder knobs\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-gum-x-mtb-tire-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Thew new Michelin Wild AM2 has been designed for mixed to softer terrain. Tall, well-spaced centre tread blocks are inspired by the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/24/michelin-dh-tyres-drop-in-with-mud-bike-park-tread-patterns-featuring-magi-x-dh-tech/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">DH34 tire</a>, chosen for their capacity to bite deep into the dirt for stability under braking in sloppy conditions. Grip and bite are prioritized over rolling resistance.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2.jpg\" alt=\"2021 michelin wild am2 all mountain mtb tire high grip slower rolling\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a>At the edge, you might notice that the shoulder blocks closely resemble those seen on the DH22 tire. Michelin say they are modified to, again, increase bite in soft conditions for increased grip, stability and progressive handling in otherwise unpredictable conditions.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll.jpg\" alt=\"michelin wild am2 deformation rock roll\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-wild-am2-rock-roll-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Both the Force AM2 and Wild AM2 tires get Michelin’s soft GUM-X compound. Though its not particularly soft to touch, it is softer than the Magi-X rubber seen on the Michelin DH 34 <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/24/michelin-dh-tyres-drop-in-with-mud-bike-park-tread-patterns-featuring-magi-x-dh-tech/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bike Park</a> tire. The GUM-X has vibration damping low-rebound properties. The dual compound is distributed so that the harder rubber sits in the centre area for rolling efficiency and durability, while a softer rubber sits at the shoulders for cornering grip.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction.jpg\" alt=\"2021 michelin wild am2 tire construction\" width=\"1200\" height=\"723\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-297x179.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-800x482.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-768x463.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-696x419.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-1068x643.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-697x420.jpg 697w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-297x179.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-800x482.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-120x72.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-768x463.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-696x419.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-1068x643.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am-tire-construction-697x420.jpg 697w\"></a></p><p>The new tires get bead-to-bead protection in the form of a dense 3 x 60 TPI casing, so should definitely be worthy of a decent beating at your local trail centre.</p><h2><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span>Michelin Force AM2</h2><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire.jpg\" alt=\"2021 michelin force am2 all mountain bike tire fast rolling\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-force-am2-mtb-tire-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a>The Michelin Force AM2 prioritizes rolling efficiency over grip, with a directional tread pattern and lower-profile elongated centre tread that doesn’t bite terrain too much. That said, those centre tread blocks are flared at the trailing edge to provide a decent braking surface.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires.jpg\" alt=\"michelin force am2 side profile\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am-2021-tires-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>At the edge, Michelin opted for <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/01/24/michelin-dh-tyres-drop-in-with-mud-bike-park-tread-patterns-featuring-magi-x-dh-tech/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">DH22</a>-inspired shoulder knobs, chosen for their grip, stability and predictable handling through corners. Michelin say they optimized the ratio between tread blocks and grooves to help maintain momentum on flowing trails.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction.jpg\" alt=\"michelin force am2 2021 mtb tire construction\" width=\"1200\" height=\"803\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-297x199.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-768x514.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-696x466.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-1068x715.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-628x420.jpg 628w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-297x199.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-800x535.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-768x514.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-696x466.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-1068x715.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/michelin-force-am2-2021-tire-construction-628x420.jpg 628w\"></a></p><h3>How do they weigh up against one another?</h3><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2.jpg\"><img loading=\"eager\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng%3Awebp%2Fngcb8%2Frs%3Adevice%2Frscb8-1\" alt=\"2021 michelin ll mountain bike tires wild am2 force am2 tread patterns\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2.jpg 1200w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-696x464.jpg 696w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-1068x712.jpg 1068w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-wild-am2-force-am2-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a>Though the pairing do look to be front and rear-specific, Michelin recommend the Force AM and Wild AM for use on either wheel. That recommendation does come with what-looks-to-be an honest little guide, telling you what kind of ride quality you can expect from the different pairings.</p><p>If you only ride chairlift or shuttle-accessed trails, likely you’ll not be too concerned with rolling efficiency. In that scenario, a double Wild AM setup might suit you best, giving you the most grip for your buck on the descents.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2.jpg\" alt=\"2021 michelin wild am2 force am2 tire\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/2021-michelin-am-tires-force-wild-am2-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>If, like most, you’re someone who has to earn their turns, rolling resistance needs to be factored in. That’s where the Force AM2 comes into the equation. On dry, manicured trail centre trails, a double Force AM2 setup will likely serve most riders well.</p><p>As someone who rides majority soft, wet, steep terrain, I’d likely opt for the double Wild AM2 combo, <em>possibly</em> considering swapping out the rear for the Force AM2 when summer makes an appearance.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Front</p></td><td><p>Rear</p></td><td><p>Grip</p></td><td><p>Rolling Efficiency</p></td><td><p>Damage Resistance</p></td><td><p>Weight</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Force AM<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Force AM<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>**</p></td><td><p>****</p></td><td><p>***</p></td><td><p>***</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wild AM<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Force AM<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>***</p></td><td><p>***</p></td><td><p>***</p></td><td><p>***</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wild AM<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>Wild AM<sup>2</sup></p></td><td><p>****</p></td><td><p>**</p></td><td><p>***</p></td><td><p>***</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>Both the Michelin Force AM2 and Wild AM2 tires are available in 27.5″ and 29″ versions, with a 2.4″ and 2.6″ option to suit a good range of rim widths.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Tyre</p></td><td><p>Size (inches and ETRTO)</p></td><td><p>Weight (g)</p></td><td><p>SRP £</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Force AM2</p></td><td><p>27.5×2.40 (61-584)</p></td><td><p>980</p></td><td><p>£47.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Force AM2</p></td><td><p>27.5×2.60 (66-584)&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td><p>1,070</p></td><td><p>£49.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Force AM2</p></td><td><p>29×2.40 (61-622)</p></td><td><p>1,040</p></td><td><p>£49.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Force AM2</p></td><td><p>29×2.60 (66-622)&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td><p>1,130</p></td><td><p>£54.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Wild AM2</p></td><td><p>27.5×2.40 (61-584)</p></td><td><p>980</p></td><td><p>£52.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Wild AM2</p></td><td><p>27.5×2.60 (66-584)&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td><p>1,070</p></td><td><p>£54.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Wild AM2</p></td><td><p>29×2.40 (61-622)</p></td><td><p>1,040</p></td><td><p>£49.99</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>MICHELIN&nbsp;Wild AM2</p></td><td><p>29×2.60 (66-622)</p></td><td><p>1,130</p></td><td><p>£54.99</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><a href=\"https://www.michelin.co.uk/bicycle/mtb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Michelin.co.uk</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"492ad6c4bdec8b2efb5627562b4f8aceb493746604bf0beeeac2a733d7325f12","category":"Cycling"}